    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for an initial 10-12 min or until almost fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-turkey-steaks-with-warm-kimchi-potato-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim your <strong>green beans</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and shake off any excess water</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-turkey-steaks-with-warm-kimchi-potato-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>and <strong>ground paprika </strong>to a plate with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-turkey-steaks-with-warm-kimchi-potato-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat your<strong> turkey breast steak</strong> dry with kitchen paper, then drizzle them with <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Press the turkey steak[s] into the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> firmly to evenly coat all over \u2013 this is your <strong>breaded turkey</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-turkey-steaks-with-warm-kimchi-potato-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>breaded turkey </strong>and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until golden and and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-turkey-steaks-with-warm-kimchi-potato-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After the potatoes have had an initial 10-12 min, add the<strong> trimmed green beans </strong>to the pot and cook for a final 3-4 min or until tender with a bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-turkey-steaks-with-warm-kimchi-potato-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>spinach </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pot with the drained potatoes</p><p>Add a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and cook for a final 1-2 min or until wilted</p><p>Once wilted, add your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar </strong>and <strong>kimchi ketchup </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>warm kimchi potato salad</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-turkey-steaks-with-warm-kimchi-potato-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crispy turkey steaks</strong> with the <strong>warm kimchi potato salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
